name: 1-phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate 5-kinase
classes: Phosphotransferases with an alcohol group as acceptor
comment: This enzyme can also phosphorylate PtdIns3P in the 4-position, and PtdIns, PtdIns3P and PtdIns(3,4)P2 in the 5-position in vitro, but to a lesser extent. The last of these reactions occurs in vivo and is physiologically relevant. Three different isoforms are known.

references.title: The diphosphoinositide kinase of rat brain.
The biosynthesis of triphosphoinositide by rat brain in vitro.
A new pathway for synthesis of phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate.
